27/08/2003
KARBALA, Iraq -- A Bulgarian battalion of 500 on Tuesday (26 August) took over control of the Iraqi holy city of Karbala from US Marines. Outgoing military governor Col Matthew Lopes passed command over to Bulgarian Lt Col Petko Marinov at a two-hour ceremony. In his address, Marinov said that his force would work to provide security to the people of the area and help them build a democratic society. Bulgarian troops in Iraq are operating under Polish command. (Dnevnik, Trud, 24 Chassa, Sega - 27/08/03; AFP, BNR - 26/08/03)
